<DOCNO> XIE19990602.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus not to Take Initiative to Forge Closer Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus said Tuesday that it will
not take any initiative aimed at forging closer ties with North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Replying to questions during his daily press briefing, Cypriot
government spokesman Costas Serezis said that "the government will
not develop any initiative in this direction."
</P>
<P>
Commenting on a statement made by Greek Foreign Undersecretary
Gregoris Niotis that NATO could participate in an international
force on the Cyprus island after an agreement is reached, Serezis
said the Cypriot government supports the deployment of a
multi-national force.
</P>
<P>
He clarified that this force should have a mandate from the
U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Turkish Cypriots-controlled
north and the greek Cypriots-dominated south since 1974 when
Turkish troops invaded and occupied the northern third of the
island in the wake of a failed coup seeking union with
Athens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
