<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 19:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OIC Concerned Over Tension in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of Islamic
Conference (OIC) Tuesday expressed concern over the growing
tension between India and Pakistan in the disputed Kashmir
region.
</P>
<P>
The Jeddah-based OIC warned against armed confrontations and
asserted support to the Kashimris for self-determination, the
Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It also called on the United Nations to help solve the dispute
over Kashmir in a bid to prevent an escalation of the conflict in
the South Asian Sub-continent.
</P>
<P>
Indian warplanes have been carrying out air strikes from last
Wednesday in Kashmir area to flush out "infiltrators" India
termed backed by Pakistan's armed forces.
</P>
<P>
New Delhi said the intruders dug in on the Indian side of the
Line of Control dividing the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
