<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Setting Up Desertification Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Technical Advisor of the Ministry of
Mines, Environment and Tourism of Zimbabwe, Mzondiwa Shoko said
Tuesday plans to set up National Environmental Desertification
Fund to counter environmental degradation are at an advanced
stage.
</P>
<P>
He said the fund was going to be set up under the National
Action Program in which the government spelt out policy and
programs on how it was going to tackle environmental and social
issues.
</P>
<P>
