used to assist rural communities in projects that deal with
environment protection, poverty alleviation and drought
mitigation.
</P>
<P>
Shoko said the fund required 6.5 million U.S. dollars to be
fully functional. About 1.3 million U.S. dollars is going to be
imbursed every year for the next five years.
</P>
<P>
There were plans to raise the 6.5 million U.S. dollars from the
donor community, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Ministry has already approved the program," he said.
</P>
