<HEADLINE> NATO Planes Hit Albanian Bunkers on Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- NATO planes dropped bombs about four
kilometers on the Albanian side of border overnight Tuesday,
destroying at least two Albanian government bunkers and some
telephone lines.
</P>
<P>
The bombs created some huge craters on the ground and the
English markings on the shrapnels revealed that it was the work of
NATO planes.
</P>
<P>
The Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)
sources were quoted as saying that seven bombs were dropped inside
Albania, with one of them bursting just 500 meters from its team.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported so far.
</P>
<P>
How NATO planes, which have been striking Serb air-defense
targets in Kosovo near the border, mistargeted the bunkers was not
known immediately.
</P>
<P>
Fierce fightings have been raging on in nearby hills around the
Morina border crossing over the past week between Serb troops and
the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA), which is seen by Belgrade as a
terrorist group.
</P>
<P>
The KLA, which has been trying to open a new supply corridor
from Albania to Prizren, 30 kilometers from the border, claimed
that with better weapons, they were much balanced with the Serb
troops now.
</P>
<P>
But the injured KLA members taken out of Kosovo into Albania
show clearly that Serb army soldiers were on their target.
</P>
<P>
With each day passes, the situation at the Morina border
crossing becomes increasingly tense and dangerous. Albanian
borderguards have evacuated from their posts to the nearby
barracks and some are seen standing under big trees.
</P>
<P>
But Kosovo refugees keep pouring into Albania through the
crossing.
</P>
<P>
In the meanwhile, an Albanian newspaper reported Tuesday that a
defused NATO bomb fell into a seaside restaurant in the Albanian
port of Durres on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
When the incident occurred, a number of people including some
Italian military policemen were eating in the restaurant, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
On Monday night, Albanian president Rexhep Meidani held an
emergency meeting to review the tense situation on the
northeastern border and discussed the measures which need to be
taken.
</P>
<P>
The meeting decided to intensify military actions against
Yugoslav troops in the border areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
