<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, the chief of General
Staff of the People's Liberation Army, in a meeting here today
with the Thai Permanent Secretary for Defense Teeradej Meepien,
said that global multi-polarization is inevitable.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that in spite of significant and profound changes in
the world today, peace and development are still the main concern.
</P>
<P>
He expressed satisfaction with the cooperation between the
Chinese and Thai armed forces and their high-level exchanges, and
said he hopes that the bilateral friendship will continue to
develop in the 21st century.
</P>
