<HEADLINE> UK Labor Costs Still Competitive in EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON June 1 (Xinhua) - Despite the strength of the pound
Britain's labor costs are still competitive against many of the
other EU states, according to a report published Tuesday by
William Mercer.
</P>
<P>
The launch of the euro has helped to expose wide differences in
labor costs across the European Union, where the highest employer
costs are nearly four times the lowest, says the consultants.
</P>
<P>
The report also shows tat the UK and the other EU states still
struggle to compete with the US employment market.
</P>
<P>
The UK appears in the middle of the ranking (eighth out of 15)
with average labor costs amounting to 35,439 euros (23,000
pounds).
</P>
<P>
In general, costs are higher in the northern European states
such as Belgium, Denmark, Sweden and Germany and lower in southern
Europe in countries such as Italy, Spain, Greece and Portugal.
</P>
<P>
The report states that with the pound strong against the euro,
"UK labor costs are still competitive against many other EU
states". 
</P>
</TEXT>
