<HEADLINE> Yemen, Belarus Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Yemen and Belarus signed here on
Tuesday an agreement on bilateral cooperation, the Yemeni News
Agency (YNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, the two sides will hold regular talks and
consultations on ways of strengthening and developing bilateral
cooperation and coordinating their stances towards various issues
of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by Yemeni Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister of Foreign Affairs Abdul Qader Ba-Jammal and his
Belarusian counterpart Ural Latypov who is now on a visit to Yemen.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, the two ministers discussed the aspects of
joint cooperation and Ba-Jammal welcomed the Belarusian
investments in the free trade zone of Aden as well as opening new
fields of cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Latypov expressed his country's readiness for
cooperation in the field of technical expertise transfer,
particularly in the area of tractor industry.
</P>
<P>
The Belarusian foreign minister arrived here on Monday.
</P>
