<HEADLINE> Pakistan Describes Situation at LoC Very Serious </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Tuesday described the
situation at the Line of Control (LoC) in Kashmir as "very
serious," and said it would continue to take appropriate measures
to defend its territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
"If they (India) tried to cross Line of Control (LoC) and
captured our positions or tried to push us back from our positions
then it would be unacceptable," Brig. Rashid Qureshi, director
general of the Inter Services Public Relations told a news
briefing here.
</P>
<P>
Responding to a question, Qureshi said the situation at LoC is
"dangerous and tense."
</P>
<P>
Over the past 36 hours, Qureshi said, there has been continuing
artillery fire from the Indian side in Kargil-Drass sector and
across rest of the LoC.
</P>
<P>
He said India launched three attacks during this time which
were beaten back. A Pakistan army captain and two soldiers died in
these offensives, he added.
</P>
<P>
"There have been eight to ten causalities in each attack from
the Indian side," said Qureshi.
</P>
<P>
The situation at the LoC in the disputed Kashmir region has
been tense since early last month when the two south Asian
neighbors exchanged fire there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
