<HEADLINE> (Urgent) Kosovo Envoys Hold Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN June 1 (Xinhua)--Three Kosovo mediators Tuesday afternoon
held their meeting in the Petersberg guest house near Bonn.
</P>
<P>
They are Russian envoy Viktor Chernomyrdin, European Union (EU)
mediator, Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari, and U.S deputy
Secretary of State Strobe Talbott.
</P>
<P>
On arriving in Bonn, Chernomyrdin said Belgrade had given a
clear signal in a letter addressed to German Foreign Minister
Joschka Fischer. Bonn's Foreign Ministry received the letter
earlier Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The letter gave the three mediators great hopes for a peaceful
solution to Kosovo crisis, said Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
"We have great hopes that there will be peace soon," he said.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade has reportedly expressed its readiness to accept the
G-8 principles on solving the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder is due to meet with the
three envoys later. More details are expected to be disclosed at
an evening press conference. 
</P>
