<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Roads Authority Signs $76.8M Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Roads Authority
Tuesday signed contract agreements for the Awash-Hirna-Dengego and
Dire Dawa-Dengego-Harar roads valued at 76.8 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued here by the authority,
works on the 141-km Awash-Hirna road and the 80-km Kulubi-Dengego
and Dire Dawa-Dengego- Harar roads will be undertaken by the China
Road and Bridge Corporation, while the 91-km Hirna-Kulubi road
project will be undertaken by Keangnam Enterprises Ltd., a firm
from the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
These road projects are scheduled to be completed within two to
three years, according to the contracts signed between the
Ethiopian Roads Authority and the two contracting firms
respectively.
</P>
<P>
These projects will be financed by the International
Development Association, the press release said, adding that the
association has financed a total of 1,388-km road projects in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
