<HEADLINE> Pak Educational Institutions near LoC Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The government of
Pakistan-administered Kashmir was forced to close all educational
institutions located near the Pakistani side of the Line of
Control (LoC) in the disputed Kashmir region.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Pakistan-administered Kashmir told the media
that the educational institutions near the LoC were closed
"because of the deliberate targeting of schools by the Indian
army."
</P>
<P>
"Other than being an inhuman act, the firing on the civil
population is also against the U.N. Charter," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said that as a result of Indian firing, ten students from
eight to ten years of age were killed in Nagdar in the Neelum
Valley Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Three students of the same ages were also killed in Narr School
in Kotli district Wednesday, the spokesman said, adding that a
large number of students were critically injured because of this
deliberate shelling on schools. 
</P>
