<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua)-- Following are highlights of
diplomatic news released by Xinhua today:
</P>
<P>
China-Russia Relations Stressed
</P>
<P>
China-Russia relations were given spotlight today as Chinese
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji met with Russian
Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov, respectively, and Foreign Minister
Tang Jiaxuan held talks and issued a joint press communique with
him.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang said that the development of the
coordinated China-Russia strategic cooperative partnership is not
only in the fundamental interest of the two peoples but also
beneficial to world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
The established Sino-Russian strategic cooperative partnership
is proceeding in a "very smooth way," Premier Zhu said, adding
that cooperation in various fields between the two neighboring
countries is also fruitful, and especially bilateral cooperation
is strengthening in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
"This cooperation is very important to both sides and to the
development of the international situation," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan told Ivanov that China is keen to
promote consultation with Russia to establish a just and
reasonable new international order and a multi-polar world.
</P>
<P>
In the joint press communique issued, the two sides reiterate
that China and Russia have no intention of forming any military or
political alliance that is directed against any third country or
bloc, and oppose the trend of the expansion and fortification of
military alliances in certain regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
