<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chendu Army Impressive while Sichuan Fo Lan Sluggish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, Anhui, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Fo Lan club of China
met with strong challenges from the NEC Blue Rockets of Japan
while another Chinese Club Chendu Army overcame a bad start to a
convincing win on the opening day of the AVC Cup Men's Club
volleyball tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan, boasting four members of the national squad, exerted
every effort to earn a triumph over NEC 25-22, 25-20, 23-25 and25-
21 while Chendu showed their characters and fighting stamina to
score a flying start 25-22, 25-11 and 25-18.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Jian'an, head coach of Sichuan, was not satisfied with the
performance of his side, saying that his spikers did not showed
their true form.
</P>
<P>
"The spikers failed to do a good teamwork with the new setter.
The internationals such as spiker Zhang Xiang, just arrived at
Hefei two days before the begining of the tournament."
</P>
<P>
He was also disappointed with the low mood of the starters in
the third set when they trailed the Japanese who are much shorter
in figure.
</P>
<P>
"They did not show enough characters and fighting stamina in
the third set which they lost," the coach said.
</P>
<P>
Chendu Army stole the light from the not-in-form Sichuan, the
reigning champions of China League, by scoring the biggest gap on
the opeing day.
</P>
<P>
The club, who finished third last season, did not start well as
they trailed 0-5, 6-10, 13-17, under the power game of the
unheralded Al Rayan of Qatar in the first set.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by the partisan crowd, the club, paced by the 37-year-
old setter Yang Liqun, fought back to level the scoring 19-all
before they earned a hard-fought 25-22 first set victory,
</P>
<P>
In the following two sets, they did not allow the Qatar side
back into the rhythm with their speed attack left unanswered.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the opener of the AVC Cup Men's Club tournament,
Samsung Fire &AMP; Insurance club of South Korea thrashed Paykan of
Iran in three sets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
