<HEADLINE> China's Duty Free Goods Sales Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China's duty free goods sales are
increasing rapidly and the figures now rank amongst the world's
top twenty best sales, according to industry sources.
</P>
<P>
It was revealed at a seminar focusing on China's duty free
business held here today that China has successfully joined the
world duty free market by setting up long-term and stable links
with more than 100 name brand goods producers from some 20
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to Gai Zhixin, general manager of the China Duty Free
Goods Company, China has set up 140 duty free shops in some 80
open ports all over the country, with a yearly sales volume of 200
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xiqin, deputy director of the National Tourism
Administration, said that the duty free sector has become an
important part of China's tourism business and an increasingly
large source of foreign exchange earnings.
</P>
<P>
Today's seminar was attended by 38 overseas duty free goods
producers and suppliers as well as some 600 representatives and
scholars from China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
