<HEADLINE> USFSA Dismisses Sexual Charges Against Coach Callaghan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Figure Skating
Association (USFSA) won't pursue sexual misconduct charges against
coach Richard Callaghan because it lacks jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Callaghan, who helped Tara Lipinski win a gold medal at last
year's Olympics, was accused by Craig Maurizi of making improper
advances while he was a teen-ager and using his authority to begin
a sexual relationship.
</P>
<P>
The USFSA dismissed Maurizi's grievance, saying he waited too
long to file it. 
</P>
