<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Reward 100 Foreign Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The State Bureau of Foreign Experts
Affairs plans to award 100 foreign experts with a "Friendship
Prize" for their outstanding services to China before the Chinese
National Day this year.
</P>
<P>
"More than 1,000 foreign experts will be invited to attend this
year's national day reception," said Zhang Yujie, deputy-director
of the State Bureau of Foreign Experts Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The system of making awards to foreign experts in China began
in the 1950s, when most of the prizes went to Russian and East
European experts. Since the reform and opening-up policy was
launched in 1978, more foreign experts from a wide range of
countries have come to work in China and by the end of 1998 a
total of 740,000 had come from more than 50 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The "Friendship Prize" has already been presented to 420
foreign experts since it was established in 1991 under the
approval of the State council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
