<DOCNO> XIE19990602.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> At Least Nine Killed in U.S. Plane Crash Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people were killed
as an American Airlines flight with 145 people aboard skidded off
a rain-slicken runway, broke apart and burst into flames in
Arkansas State of the United States before midnight Tuesday, the
Associated Press (AP) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Some 80 people were injured and taken to hospitals, and 14 were
not immediately accounted for. Fifty-one others did not require
hospital treatment.
</P>
<P>
Flight 1420, a Super MD-80, had 139 passengers and six crew
members and was due to arrive in Little Rock City at 9:41 p.m.(
local time). The flight from Dallas of Texas State was delayed
for more than two hours and arrived just as the storm was hitting
the city with lightning, hail and winds gusting to nearly 90 mph (
145 kph).
</P>
<P>
Passengers described a scene of terror, with the twin-engine
jetliner splitting into pieces and catching fire after it slid to
the edge of the Arkansas River. Some passengers squeezed one by
one through an emergency exit as flames spread through the plane.
</P>
<P>
The deaths are the first in an U.S. commercial airline accident
since December 28, 1997, when a woman was killed aboard a United
Airlines 747 that encountered severe turbulence over the Pacific.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990602.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build World's First Tidal Power Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The world's first tidal power
station will be built in the Zhoushan islands area of east coastal
China's Zhejiang Province, the Zhejiang Provincial Bureau of
Oceanography said today.
</P>
<P>
The Zhoushan islands have one of the world's richest tidal
energy resources, and the site is determined after two years of
investigations by Chinese and foreign experts, according to the
bureau.
</P>
<P>
The power station project will be designed and built by several
Chinese research institutes in collaboration with Italy's Ponte Di
Archinede Company, and is expected to start generating electricity
in the early next century.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the world's island regions usually lack of
energy resources like oil, coal and hydraulic resources. In China
one third of the inhabited coastal islands still have no
electricity supply.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
