<DOCNO> XIE19990602.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Index Sheds 3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Karachi Stock
Exchange (KSE) shed another 3.3 percent on Wednesday amid concerns
over uncertain situation in Kashmir and tariff dispute between
Hubco, the largest private power producing company in Pakistan,
and the government.
</P>
<P>
The KSE 100 share price index declined 39.18 points to 1140.77
points from Tuesday's 1179.95 points with a volume rising to
184.453 million shares from 130.753 million shares.
</P>
<P>
"The market was weak throughout the day due to news that Hubco
has sent a notice of default to the Water and Power Development
Authority (Wapda) for which the people believed that tariff
dispute will remain unresolved," said Shakeel Anwar Kamal, a
dealer with Prudential Securities Pvt. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Hubco on Tuesday afternoon confirmed that the Wapda has failed
to establish letter of credit in favor of the company under a
power purchase agreement between them.
</P>
<P>
Share price of Hubco fell 3.9 percent to 16.90 rupees from
17.60 rupees.
</P>
<P>
Of the 146 active issues, gainers managed to beat losers 58 to
45 while 43 remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
