<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Thai Deputy Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian said here today that friendship and cooperation between
China and Thailand and their armed forces will benefit peace and
stability in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with Teeradej Meepien, permanent secretary for
defense of Thailand, Chi reiterated the Chinese government's
stance towards the U.S.-led NATO's attack on the Chinese embassy
in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Teeradej tendered his regret for the attack on the Chinese
embassy and expressed his understanding and support for the
indignation and demands of the Chinese government and people for a
correct and full apology and inquiry.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope that the friendship between his country
and China, and their armed forces, will continue to develop no
matter how the world changes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
