<HEADLINE> China IT Industry Forms League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- An IT industry League, initiated by
the China IT Chamber of Commerce and 50 famous IT enterprises and
institutions, was launched here today.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the formation of the digitized industry
league will spur far-reaching internal integration of the domestic
makers of computers, telecommunications equipment and household
appliances.
</P>
<P>
China's IT industry has recorded an average growth of 30
percent in recent years. Internet users have now reached 2.1
million and 15 million computers have been installed across the
country.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, VCDs and mobile phone sales have achieved
stunning growths. And there has appeared a tendency toward
integration of computers, telecommunications and consumer
electronics.
</P>
<P>
China was in urgent need of an industry group to serve as a
bridge between government departments, institutions, enterprises
and consumers and regulate market behavior, experts said.
</P>
<P>
The league will fill the void and further promote the
development of the IT industry in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
