<HEADLINE> Guangdong Electronics Maker Issues New Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China's laregest maker of cooling
equipment, Guangdong Kelong Electronics Co. Ltd. raised 1.07
billion yuan today from its offer of 110 million shares on the
Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Kelong, based in Shunde City of China's southern province of
Guangdong, also ranks among the top 10 refrigerator producers in
the world, and has a yearly production capacity of 2.8 million
refrigerators and 600,000 air conditioners at present.
</P>
<P>
According to company sources, 800 million yuan of the money
raised will be spent on the acquisition of two other companies'
assets and about 100 million on the expansion of 2,000 sales and
service outlets across the country.
</P>
<P>
The acquisition is expected to increase Kelong's annual
capacity of air conditioner production and sales to 1.5 million
set by the year 2000, sources said.
</P>
<P>
Kelong, which is also listed on the stock exchange of Hong Kong,
expects its revenue to reach 4.06 billion yuan this year, up 18.8
percent over that of last year, and its net profit up 12 percent
to 660 million yuan.  
</P>
