<HEADLINE> Visitors in Tour Groups to Macao Decrease in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of visitors in tour groups
to Macao was 82,470 in April, down 3.2 percent from the same month
of 1998, the latest official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released today by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department, those coming from China's mainland areas,
Taiwan and Hong Kong accounted for 84.8 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
However, visitors to Macao in tour groups in the first four
months of the year as a whole were 333,794, an increase of 12.4
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, 10,139 Macao residents, out of a population
of some 430,000, traveled to other places in tour groups in April.
The figure rose 6.5 percent over the same month of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The most favored destinations of Macao residents were China's
mainland areas (78.1 percent), Taiwan (6.3 percent) and Thailand (
3.8 percent).
</P>
<P>
During the first four months of this year, the number of Macao
residents traveled to other places in tour groups increased 17.1
percent over the same period of 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
