<HEADLINE> Fund-Raising Setup Urged for Defence Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- As a matter of urgency China should
quickly set up a multi-channel fund-raising mechanism for the
research and development of defence-oriented high technology,
according to specialists.
</P>
<P>
The call for action came from delegates to a symposium on
scientific inventions, risk investment and defence construction
which was attended by more than 30 experts from the military,
government departments, the People's bank of China and research
institutions.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that in the wake of the U.S.-led NATO
attacking on the Chinese embassy in Belgrade, significant changes
have taken place in both the international and domestic political
and economic situation and that the Chinese government should
seize this opportunity to take timely measures to boost national
defence, and set up more channels to raise funds for the research
and development of defence-oriented high technologies.
</P>
<P>
They said that this will also provide many job opportunities
for the country at present.
</P>
<P>
In the present era of knowledge-based economy, the delegates
said, the research and development of military high technologies
needed by modern national defence will serve as a great impetus to
the growth of the overall economy.  
</P>
