<HEADLINE> APEC Investment Fair Opens in Seoul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The "APEC (Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation) Investment Mart 1999" opens here with the attendance
of some 2,500 representatives from across the world.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at the opening of the fair, President Kim said
the event, the first of its kind in the world, will be a trigger
to attract much more foreign investors into the Asia-Pacific
region by announcing economic recovery to the world and by
enhancing its international credibility.
</P>
<P>
The APEC Investment Mart will serve as the momentum for the
strengthening of economic ties among the APEC members themselves
and between the nations of the region and other countries around
the world, said Kim.
</P>
<P>
"The Asian economy has emerged from the depths of the foreign
currency crisis, however, and its vitality will soon be fully
restored. Asia has resolutely changed the weak economic factors
that invited the crisis and has high hopes for a new leap forward
based on strong self-confidence," the South Korean president said.
</P>
<P>
The four-day fair featuring 1,448 investment projects from 21
members of APEC is the first one held in South Korea.
</P>
<P>
The 21 APEC members set up their own booths occupying 300
square meters each at Seoul Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The fair was proposed by President Kim Dae-jung in the 6th
summit of APEC members last November in Kuala Lumpur to
facilitate investment in the region. 
</P>
