<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian official said Wednesday
the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) expects the new Israeli
government to announce its policy regarding the expansion of
Jewish settlements initiated by the outgoing Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
PNA Minister of Local Government Saeb Erekat said the
Palestinian authority hopes Israeli prime minister-elect Ehud
Barak and his new cabinet to take a clear stand on the settlement
issue to re-activate the peace process.
</P>
<P>
In statements broadcast by Voice of Palestine radio on
Wednesday, Erakat asserted the peace process requires a cessation
of all Jewish settlement activities in the Israeli-occupied
territories, as well as the implementation of the Wye River accord.
</P>
