Erakat, the chief Palestinian negotiator with Israel, also
renewed the PNA's demand that Barak and his future cabinet
abolish all settlement plans.
</P>
<P>
The number of Israeli settlements in the West Bank has exceeded
170 whereas the number of settlers is well over 170,000 by the end
of 1998, according to statistics released by the Israeli Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Israel on Tuesday said Barak and his
future cabinet may adopt a policy regarding settlements which will
allow the development of natural resources and the expansion of
existing settlements but prohibit the establishment of new ones.
