<HEADLINE> Editorial: China Upholds Independent Foreign Policy of Peace (Part 1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thursday issue of People's
Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial entitled
"Unswervingly Upholding Independent Foreign Policy of Peace".
</P>
<P>
The editorial says the U.S.-led NATO attack on the Chinese
Embassy in Belgrade was a serious invasion of China's sovereignty
and a major challenge to China's independent foreign policy of
peace.
</P>
<P>
It points out that the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC), with Jiang Zemin at the core, rapidly and properly
tackled this major issue, which indicated China's firm stand on
maintaining peace and against hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin again stressed at a meeting for welcoming
diplomatic personnel from the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia that
China will continue to unswervingly uphold its independent foreign
policy of peace.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says Jiang's remarks are a guideline for handling
China's foreign affairs at the turn of this century.
</P>
<P>
The article says peace and development are two major issues
today. However, neither of them has been solved.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-led NATO has been advocating such fallacies as "state
sovereignty is not as important as human rights" and "limited
sovereignty" and it has been trying to violate the principle of
non-interference in other countries' internal affairs and lay "
theoretical" foundations for interference in other countries'
affairs and invasion of other countries.
</P>
<P>
China believes that a country, small or large, should be
treated equally and its sovereignty and integrity of territory
should be respected.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990602.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Editorial: China Upholds Independent Foreign Policy of Peace (Part 2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The editorial points out that it is an important part of
China's independent foreign policy of peace to fight against
hegemonism and power politics.
</P>
<P>
However, the U.S.-led NATO attack on the Chinese Embassy in
Belgrade showed that hegemonism and power politics are major
threats to world peace.
</P>
<P>
In dealing with international affairs, the editorial says,
China has to decide its own stand and policy on the basis of the
fundamental interests of the Chinese people and people in other
countries of the world, without caring about the attitudes of
other countries.
</P>
<P>
China will firmly struggle against hegemonism and work for
maintaining world peace without fear of pressure.
</P>
<P>
The article says, "Upholding the independent foreign policy of
peace also covers promoting friendly cooperation with Western
countries including the United States.
</P>
<P>
"So long as they are willing to implement the Five Principles
of Peaceful Coexistence, China is ready to establish cooperative
relations in various fields with them."
</P>
<P>
The development trend of the Sino-U.S. relations, the editorial
says, is of great importance to the whole world. Though the
improvement and development of the Sino-U.S. ties has experienced
ups and downs and there are anti-China forces in the United States,
the vast number of the American people believe in having friendly
ties with China.
</P>
<P>
China will oppose hegemonism while promoting ties with the
United States and this act indicates China's firm stance, its
flexibility in handling foreign affairs as well as its maturity
and confidence in its relations with other countries.
</P>
<P>
The editorial emphasizes that under the CPC Central Committee's
leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core, China will hold higher
the banner of an independent foreign policy of peace and make
greater contributions to the maintaining of the sovereignty and
dignity of the Chinese nation, the noble undertakings of world
peace and the development of mankind.  
</P>
