<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 80,000 Chinese and
foreign tourists have come to Haining, east China's Zhejiang
Province, to watch the unusual night tides of Qiantang River over
the past five days.
</P>
<P>
