<HEADLINE> All-China Women's Federation Conferred UN Environmental Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese delegation will fly to
Tokyo tomorrow to attend the "Global 500 Award" and "International
Environmental Day" celebration ceremony organized by the United
Nations Environment Program (UNEP).
</P>
<P>
The delegation will receive the annual "Global 500 Award"
conferred by the UNEP at the ceremony, which is to be held on June
5.
</P>
<P>
The All-China Women's Federation has been given the
environmental award this year for its efforts and outstanding
achievements in environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The federation has been organizing some 120 million Chinese
women to plant trees each year since 1990. More than five billion
trees have been planted, covering an area of over four million
hectares due to its efforts.
</P>
<P>
The federation's work in increasing women's environmental
awareness has also received high praise from the UNEP.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation, consisting of officials from the
federation and the State Environmental Protection Administration,
will exchange experience in environmental improvement with
delegations from other countries during the meeting.  
</P>
