<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Russian FM (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin told
Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov that the development of the
coordinated China-Russia strategic partnership is not only in the
fundamental interest of the two peoples but also beneficial to
world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark during his meeting with Ivanov at the
Diaoyutai State Guesthouse here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang first asked Ivanov to convey his regards to Russian
President Boris Yeltsin. "The Chinese government and people is
expecting President Yeltsin to visit China again this autumn," the
Chinese leader said.
</P>
<P>
He confirmed that the current Sino-Russian ties have witnessed
smooth growth with frequent exchanges and cooperation spreading in
all fields, adding that China is willing to make concerted efforts
with Russia for further development of such relationships.
</P>
<P>
Jiang indicated that certain complex changes have occurred in
the international arena. "The U.S.-led NATO's bombing against
Yugoslavia and their attack on the Chinese embassy in Belgrade
made people see more clearly the vanity of what they flaunted as
'democracy' and 'human rights'," he stated.
</P>
<P>
"Currently, the bombing against Yugoslavia continues and
civilian casualties have increased in large numbers," he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the U.S.-led NATO should stop bombing
immediately so as to create the necessary conditions for a
political solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
