<HEADLINE> Thailand Names Snooker Squad for SEA Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Snooker Association of Thailand
(SAT) has announced 18 players to carry the Thai flag into
August's SEA Games in Brunei and vowed to produce at least three
gold medals in the 20th regional sport extravaganza, The Nation
reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, the association also set strict guidelines to keep its
athletes in check by threatening to axe players who violate the
association's rules three times, even if they were gold-medal
prospects.
</P>
<P>
"Players who break the rules for the first time will receive a
warning. If they break the rules a second time, 30 percent of
their allowance will be cut, and if they contravene regulations
again, they will be removed from the team," assistant team manager
Anek Roowatananon said.
</P>
<P>
Former SEA Games champion Choochart Trairattanapradit was named
snooker team's coach, and one-time billiards gold-medallist
Mongkol Kanfaklang was selected as supervisor of the billiards
team.
</P>
<P>
Choochart predicted Thailand should win three of the 10 gold
medals on offer in the Games, including two from snooker and one
from billiards.
</P>
<P>
However, he said it still depends on the performance of
Thailand's arch-rivals Indonesia, the Philippines and Malaysia.
</P>
</TEXT>
