<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Auto Parts Show Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Auto experts from China and across
the world have flocked to the Auto Parts, Manufacturing and
Related Products Show 1999 which opened at Beijing's International
Exhibition Center today.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 companies attending the show are mostly from
China but with more than 20 from other countries and regions
including the United States, Germany, Japan, Austria, the Republic
of Korea, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Director-General Shao Qihui and Deputy Director-General Zhang
Xiaoyu of the State Administration of Machinery Industry attended
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that China's auto parts industry is still lagging
behind advanced international levels. He hopes that the show will
help enhance exchange and cooperation between Chinese and foreign
auto companies so as to promote the development of the local auto
industry.
</P>
<P>
Participants are displaying such products as auto parts,
product development technologies, new materials and techniques,
processing equipment, maintenance and test equipment and auto
accessories.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the major bus makers in China are present with
strong delegations. The luxury bus industry has been greatly
promoted by the rapid expansion of super highways around the
country in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Spanish joint venture bus maker Irizar-Tianjin caught
the attention of spectators with a 1.7 million yuan luxury bus.
General Manager Aleja Ganzalez Anso said that as one of the most
well known bus makers in Europe, Irizar will bring advanced
management technology into China so as to help the country train
talents and develop new products.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-French joint venture Dongfeng-Citroen launched a new
car at the show today. It is the second joint venture auto company
that is manufacturing automatic cars in China, following at the
heels of the Sino-German joint venture FAW-Volkswagen.
</P>
<P>
Other exhibits at the show include a cross-field wheeled
carrier used by China's armed forces, the first time that the
heavy duty vehicle has been seen at an international exhibition.
The vehicle, which combines Chinese and foreign technologies, won
a national prize for scientific advancement. It was developed by
the China National Heavy Duty Truck Industry Group. Officers from
the armed forces said that the vehicle performs excellently in the
field.
</P>
<P>
The show, which ends on June 7, is being staged by the State
Administration of Machinery Industry, China National Automotive
Industry Corp., China Council for the Promotion of International
Trade and China Association of Automobile Manufacturers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
