<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian FMs Issue Joint Press Communique (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
7. The two sides oppose any method to push forward power
politics and stress the need to earnestly respect the choice of
social systems, sense of values and development path of all
peoples on the basis of their national condition.
</P>
<P>
The two sides believe that the world cannot be reorganized into
one overall pattern. Only by respecting the sovereignty and
territorial integrity of all countries, big or small, strong or
weak, neutral or non-aligned, and by not allowing interference in
the internal affairs of sovereign states in violation of the U.N.
Charter and U.N. resolutions and with pretexts such as "protecting
basic values," or "safeguarding" human rights or rights of
minority groups, can peace and stability of the contemporary world
be protected.
</P>
<P>
8. The two sides express the view that their essential goal is
to establish the Sino-Russian strategic cooperative partnership
which is aimed at building up multi-polarization and a just and
fair international order; safeguard world peace, stability and
security; and promote a common development of the countries
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reiterate that China and Russia have no intention
of forming any military or political alliance with any third
country or bloc as the target, and oppose the trend of the
expansion and fortification of military alliances in certain
regions.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov extended gratitude for the hospitable reception he had
been given by the Chinese side and invited Tang to pay an official
visit to Russia which was gratefully accepted. Date of the visit
will be decided through diplomatic channels.  
</P>
</TEXT>
