<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian FMs Issue Joint Press Communique (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan and Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov issued a joint
press communique in the wake of their talks here today.
</P>
<P>
The following is the full text:
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan,
Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov is paying an official visit
to the People's Republic of China between June 1 and 3.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji met with
Ivanov and foreign ministers from both countries also held talks
in which they exchanged views on bilateral ties and major issues
concerning the international situation.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have reached the following consensus:
</P>
<P>
1. The first informal meeting between Chinese President Jiang
Zemin and Russian President Boris Yeltsin in November 1998 in
Moscow greatly promoted the growth of bilateral ties. The views on
the international situation as expounded by the two heads of state
in the joint declaration entitled China-Russia Relations in the
Trans-century Period bore realistic significance.
</P>
<P>
2. The two sides agree that the second informal meeting between
the two heads of state will make concrete contributions to the
further development of the China-Russia strategic cooperative
partnership. The two sides will make full preparations for the
meeting.
</P>
