<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6th China National Art Festival For New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The 6th China National Art Festival
is to be held in October of 2000 in east China's Jiangsu Province,
the first state-level art festival to be held in the new
millennium and the first in China's economically booming southern
coastal area.
</P>
<P>
Co-sponsored by the Ministry of Culture and Jiangsu Provincial
People's Government, the 12-day festival will be based in Nanjing,
capital of Jiangsu, with the nearby Suzhou, Wuxi, Changzhou and
Yangzhou as the supporting cites, according to a news conference
today.
</P>
<P>
Some 80 performances will be presented from inland areas, Hong
Kong, Macao and Taiwan region and abroad, incorporating various
artistic forms such as dramas, Chinese operas, foreign operas,
dances, acrobatics, and so on. They will all compete for the China
National Art Award and other prizes at the festival.
</P>
<P>
An international Chinese painting and calligraphy competition
and seminars on art will also be held, hoping to attract more than
30,000 participants to the historical event.
</P>
<P>
As a state-level art festival, China National Art Festival has
been previously successfully held in Beijing, Kunming, Lanzhou and
Chengdu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
