<HEADLINE> China Requires Qualifications for Certain Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Labor and Social
Security (MLSS) has recently introduced a set of regulations
governing the qualifications required for a total of 66 different
professions to improve the efficiency and quality of those
positions.
</P>
<P>
An MLSS official said that those who want to be employed in
these professions must first receive one to three years'
vocational training and obtain certificates.
</P>
<P>
The professions are mostly technically-oriented, including
lathe operators, millers, garagemen, fitters, auto drivers,
photographers and secretaries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the work units which employ personnel without
qualification certificates will be punished and ordered to correct
the malpractice. 
</P>
