<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: CDMA Forerunners Eye Asia Market (1) By Lu Jin and Tao Wenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- In the eyes of some
telecommunication giants, their new darling technology CDMA (code-
division multiple-access) is on its way to a boom in the Asia
Pacific.
</P>
<P>
Executives of some of the world's leading providers of
telecommunications service and products have expressed their
optimism and confidence in the prospects about CDMA market in
China and the rest of the Asia Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
The development of CDMA, a continuous digital transmission
technology, in the Asia Pacific region is dramatic, said Terry Yen,
a member of the CDMA Development Group (CDG), which is to convene
its fourth annual World Congress in Hong Kong in mid-June.
</P>
<P>
CDMA is a traditionally U.S.-based technology, but a lot of the
first-class world technologies have been put into use in Asia, Yen
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the CDG, the worldwide subscribers of its flagship
technology, cdmaOne, totaled 29 million at the end of March this
year, a one-year increase of over 300 percent.
</P>
<P>
The rapid growth of the technology is occurring in every
region in the world with the Asia Pacific leading the way with a
one-year net increase of 10.9 million. Worldwide, operators have
added more than 19 million subscribers since March of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Yen said that the annual CDMA World Congress to be held in Hong
Kong between June 14 and 18 will be the "most important event for
the CDMA industry."
</P>
<P>
Companies of the industry want to use this opportunity to
exchange information and experience among the CDMA community, Yen
said.
</P>
<P>
"In many ways Asia is our home with the first CDMA network
being launched here by (local telecom company) Hutchison in Hong
Kong and it's natural for us to focus on Hong Kong for this
congress," he added.
</P>
<P>
Company executives believed that the opening of the Chinese
market is very attractive and many companies want to use Hong Kong
as a hub for a lot of high technologies to enter the China market.
</P>
<P>
The CDMA technology is, for this region, a fast growing
technology year on year, said Thomas Hinton, vice president and
general manager of greater China Network Solutions Division of
Motorola.
</P>
<P>
The nationwide CDMA launch in Japan is "astonishing" with
networks having been set up recently, he said. Their No. 1 selling
phones produced by Hitachi are sold out months in advance.
</P>
<P>
The CDG said Tuesday that cdmaOne technology has gained
significant momentum in Japan as a result of the recent cdmaOne
nationwide service launch.
</P>
<P>
The Republic of Korea has the largest population of CDMA users
in the world in contrast to its geographically small size.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, the entire region will benefit from the recent
third generation (3G) harmonization efforts as cdmaOne is the only
technology offering a seamless evolution path with the ability to
deploy 3G services in existing spectrum bands.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
