<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Mobile Phone Users Exceed 30 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of mobile phone users in
China has been on a constant rise in recent years and now exceeds
30 million, ranking third in the world after the United States and
Japan.
</P>
<P>
Since mobile telecommunications were introduced to China in
1987, business has grown 100 percent on an annual basis, according
to Feng Yu, an official in the Ministry of Information Industry.
</P>
<P>
Even greater potential is yet to be tapped as the popularity
rate of mobile phones in China remains below 3 percent in terms of
population.
</P>
<P>
Experts project that the number of mobile phone users in China
will reach 46 million at the turn of the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
