<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers on Wednesday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- About 20 percent of chicken farms in Belgium have been
contaminated by the toxic dioxin material. Even if the risks for
the health of consumers remain minimum, the European veterinary
committee will decide on Wednesday whether it will impose an
embargo on export of Belgian chickens.
</P>
<P>
-- A poll realized by the Ipsos polling institution and
Liberation shows that the feeling for a unified Europe is gaining
ground, especially among European youths. The poll shows that
public opinions in European countries, except Britain, support the
construction of European Union.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa's second democratic and multi-racial general
election will be held on Wednesday, in which the African National
Congress is widely expected to win. The parliament deputies to be
elected are expected to designate on June 14 Vice President Thabo
Mbeki as the successor of President Nelson Mandela.
</P>
<P>
-- Tension continues to rise between French hunters and Green
Party. The head of the list of Greens candidates for the European
Parliament election, Daniel Cohn-Bendit, canceled an electoral
meeting in Bordeaux Tuesday evening because of threats of
provocation from hunters. 
</P>
