<HEADLINE> 5 NATO Warplanes Arrive at Bandirma Base in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Five NATO F-16 warplanes Wednesday
arrived at Bandirma military base in western Turkey as part of the
military group's plan to expand air attacks against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
A total of 18 American warplanes will be deployed at the base
in western Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On May 31, U.S. warplanes began to arrive at Balikesir Air Base
in western Turkey to launch air strikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 36 fighter jets will be deployed at the
Balikesir military base.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, C-5 and C-17 cargo planes belonging to the U.S.
Air Forces carried logistic materials and NATO soldiers to the
Balikesir base for air operations against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The North Atlantic Treaty Organization decided to deploy a
total of 72 fighter jets, including 18 Turkish warplanes at three
Turkish military bases for its air campaign against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-led western military bloc is expected to launch
attacks on the targets in Yugoslavia from Turkey via an air
corridor over Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,000 U.S. personnel will soon arrive at the
military bases in Balikesir and Bandirma in western Turkey.
</P>
</TEXT>
