<HEADLINE> Hainan Farmers Attend Technology Training Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- South China's Hainan Province
sponsored 100 farming skill training programs for one million
local farmers during 1998.
</P>
<P>
The programs covered planting, animal husbandry, ocean fishing,
processing and farm machinery. The programs led to the development
of a variety of new agricultural products and the average 1998
income of local farmers grew to 2,515 yuan (303 US dollars), up
193 yuan on 1997.
</P>
<P>
The province allocated 10.11 million yuan worth of teaching
materials, including 310,000 training manuals, 100,000 wall charts,
400 VCDs and 640,000 supplementary pamphlets.
</P>
<P>
Related departments organized 570 experts to give lectures
during the training courses. Experts visited fields and village
schools to present easily understandable practical knowledge
related to grain crops, vegetables, aquatic products, fruit,
tropical plants, pastures and farm machinery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
