<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Malaysian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met here
this morning with visiting Malaysian Foreign Minister Syed Hamid
Albar.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 25th anniversary of establishment of
diplomatic ties between China and Malaysia and he had received a
warm letter of congratulations from his Malaysian counterpart
Mahathir bin Mohamad to mark the occasion.
</P>
<P>
"During the 25 years, bilateral relations have developed
smoothly," Zhu said. He mentioned in particular the Sino-Malaysian
joint statement signed during Syed's current visit to China,
saying that the document indicated directions for the future
development of Sino-Malaysian relationships. This is very
significant and China is happy about it, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
On the trade and economic relations between the two countries,
Zhu said that bilateral cooperation has great potential and some
key cooperation projects are being carried out. "Cooperation in
other fields, which also have broad prospects, have been gradually
carried out," he added.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia has played an important and active role in
international and regional affairs, the Chinese leader said,
adding that China values very much its all-round cooperation with
Malaysia and is willing to join Malaysia to make its due
contribution to safeguarding regional peace, stability and
development.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also expressed his congratulations for the active results
achieved by Malaysia in implementing an economic recovery program
to meet its own national needs.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, he briefed the guests on China's economic
situation and its views on the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Syed said that the two countries enjoy very good relations and
the mutual trust and understanding between the leaders of the two
countries have created favorable conditions for the smooth growth
of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian foreign minister extended gratitude for China's
contribution to regional economic stability and recovery and
expressed his willingness to strengthen cooperation with China in
all fields.
</P>
<P>
Syed conveyed cordial regards from Mahathir to Zhu who
expressed thanks and asked Syed to convey his cordial regards to
his Malaysian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
Syed and his party have left Beijing for Shanghai today to
continue their visit to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
