<HEADLINE> China Approves Fewer Overseas-funded Enterprises  in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua)-- A recent report released by the
State Administration of Industry and Commerce showed that China
approved 3,271 overseas-funded enterprises during the first
quarter of the year, down 16.9 percent on the 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises involved total funding of 5.15 billion US
dollars, down 12.7 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese real estate sector was the most attractive sector
for overseas investment. The number of companies approved for the
sector grew 15.67 percent during the period, with funding rising
by 88.4 percent. 
