<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Sierra Leone President (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua)-- China treasures its traditional
friendship with Sierra Leone and is ready to make concerted
efforts to further bilateral friendly cooperative ties in a long-
term and stable way, China's top legislator Li Peng said here
today.
</P>
<P>
In a cordial and friendly meeting with visiting Sierra Leone
President Ahmad Tejan Kabbah, Li, Chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said he believed
Kabbah's visit serves to increase mutual understanding and promote
bilateral friendly relations of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li said that both China and Sierra Leone, as developing nations,
support each other on the international arena and make joint
efforts to safeguard the national rights of developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese NPC and the Sierra Leone House of Representatives
have maintained friendly relations, he said, adding he is
expecting the speaker's visit to China due in August this year.
</P>
<P>
Strengthening contacts between the two parliaments is conducive
to increasing understanding between the two peoples and promoting
the friendly relations of cooperation between the two nations, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that when he played host to the president of Cote
d'Ivoire National Assembly not long ago, he was introduced to the
situation in western Africa. Li said he was told that some
countries, including Sierra Leone, are striving to end their war
conflicts and realize peace, and have made some progress in this
process.
