<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Agency to Fund Population Program in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Population Fund
(UNFPA) is funding a population program in Kenya at a cost of 20
million U.S. dollars, the agency's country representative Sidiki
Coulibaly has said.
</P>
<P>
The program is scheduled to go on until 2001 and out of the
total amount, 16.5 million dollars will come from UNFPA regular
resources, the East African Standard newspapers reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to a report issued to the press Tuesday by UNFPA, the
program will be the fifth cycle of assistance to Kenya and the
U.N. organization will get the balance of 3.5 million dollars from
multi-lateral agencies.
</P>
<P>
Coulibaly said the program would stress on reproductive health,
safe motherhood, adolescents and youth reproductive health needs
and the prevention of the spread of AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Kenya has experienced a positive demographic transition among
sub-Sahara African countries, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
