<HEADLINE> Philippine Central Bank Governor Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
Wednesday announced the appointment of Rafael Buenaventura as the
new governor of the Central Bank of the Philippines, effective
upon the retirement of Governor Gabriel Singson on July 5, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Estrada made the announcement prior to his departure for Japan
to begin a four-day visit.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the appointment of Buenaventura, currently
President of PCI Bank, Estrada described Buenavetura as a seasoned
banker.
</P>
<P>
"In the course of his service as a former president of the
Bankers Association of the Philippines, and as former senior
officer of Citibank in southeast Asia and Europe, he has developed
broad international contacts in the financial community," Estrada
said.
</P>
<P>
Estrada also commended Governor Singson for his "outstanding
career in central banking."
</P>
<P>
Estrada said Singson's leadership helped stabilize the currency
and banking system in the midst of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Singson has agreed to serve as a senior adviser to the central
bank on a part-time basis following his retirement as governor, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
