<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Real Estate Prices Slipping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua)-- The prices of Chinese residential
houses have been falling since the beginning of the year as more
real estate companies are revising their sales strategy following
a decrease in purchases.
</P>
<P>
The average price for an apartment in China was 1,967 yuan per
square meter in April. This is the first time the price has fallen
below the 2,000 yuan per square meter level.
</P>
<P>
During the January-April period, China had 65.05 million sq.m.
of unsold residential houses, up 24.1 percent over the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Over the four months, China sold 15.34 million sq.m., up 17.6
percent over the same period last year. Last year, the growth rate
for the same period was 39.9 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
