<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Russian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua)-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
Wednesday afternoon with visiting Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov conveyed president Boris Yeltsin's regards to Jiang and
said Yeltsin is expected to meet Jiang at a earlier date.
</P>
<P>
The Russian foreign minister said the current international
situation shows that the establishment of Russia-China strategic
partnership by the two heads of state is very important and the
smooth development of the Russia-China relationship is of
extremely important role in stabilizing the international
situation.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is still going on at press time and the two sides
are expected to exchange views on a wide-range of regional and
international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan
met with Ivanov respectively this morning.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov arrived here Tuesday for a three-day official visit.
</P>
