<HEADLINE> 3 More Children Killed In Kashmir by Indian Shelling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 2 (Xinhua) -- At least three school children
were killed and four others injured Wednesday when Indian
artillery firing hit civilian areas in Nikyal sector in
Pakistan-controlled Kashmir, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from the Line of Control (LoC) area,
Indian forces started artillery firing on the border towns in
Pakistan-administered part of Kashmir at 7 a.m. local time (0200
GMT).
</P>
<P>
A mortar shell hit the small town of Nara Mora and killed three
students, who were on their way to school, said the reports,
adding that four other people, including two women, were injured
in the shelling.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Office condemned India for killing seven
school children with mortar shelling Tuesday in Neelam valley in
pakistan-controlled Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Around 100 Kashmiris Wednesday held a rally in front of the
Indian High Commission in Islamabad, protesting India over the
killing of school children.
</P>
<P>
A speaker for the rally said that Kashmiris are not intruders
and called for the international community to intervene for the
settlement of the Kashmir dispute between Pakistan and India.
</P>
</TEXT>
