<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Receive 11.13 Mln Dollar Grant from EC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC) will
provide 540 million taka (11.13 million U.S. dollars) as grant in
support of the Bangladeshi government's initiative to improve
reproduction health, the Financial Express daily reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Antonio de Souza Menezes, head of an EC delegation, told a
workshop here Tuesday that this grant is part of the EC commitment
towards the Health and Population Sector Program of the
Bangladeshi government.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be used to guarantee a reliable supply and
availability of high quality condoms to the population, Menezes
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh has a population of 126 million living on 148,393
square kilometers of land and its population density is one of the
highest in the world. The annual growth rate of the population has
come down to 1.75 percent with the acceptance of family planning
practices rising to 48.7 percent since the Bangladeshi government
has attached great importance to family planning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
