<HEADLINE> Digital Technology Enters New Arena </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- New breakthroughs in digital
imaging technology allows consumers to present relatives or
friends with cakes imprinted with photographs, pictures and even
love letters.
</P>
<P>
A recent issue of Science Times reported that bakeries in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, recently
introduced the use of related digital imaging technology.
</P>
<P>
The technology allows bakers to scan and imprint images on
edible paper which is then placed on the face of a cake.
</P>
<P>
The paper melt within 30 minutes leaving an image on the cake,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Experts expect that digital imaging technology which allows
users to store and manipulate images on their personal computers
will gain increasing popularity in China during 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
