<HEADLINE> Shanghai Establishes Over 300 Air Links </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Some 22 domestic and 23 foreign
airlines operate regularly scheduled flights linking Shanghai, one
of China's leading air hubs, with 101 domestic and foreign cities.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 percent of flights arriving at or departing
Shanghai's Hongqiao Airport fly return routes from foreign
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Holland's 80-year-old Royal Dutch Airlines introduced a flight
from Amsterdam to Shanghai in March to resume the Sino-Dutch air
route after a 50 year interruption.
</P>
<P>
European airlines, including German-based Lufthansa, French
Airlines, Austrian Airlines and Italian Airlines operate cargo
flights to Shanghai. Foreign airways offer 20 weekly flights
between Europe and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The new international airport in the Pudong New Areas is
scheduled to open in late December and will greatly expand local
air services.  
</P>
