<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The World Bank on Tuesday announced the approval
of a credit totaling 32 million U.S. dollars for the Bangladesh
Export Diversification project that will help the South Asian
country expand the range, depth, and quantity of exports.
</P>
<P>
The bank said in a statement that the project will help speed
Bangladesh's integration into the world economy by giving the
country's entrepreneurs the know-how they need to gain greater
access to world markets and by making public policies and
institutions more supportive to export needs. (WB-Bangladesh)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- Global institutional equity holdings grew 23
percent in 1998 to a value of 14.9 trillion U.S. dollars,
exceeding the 18 percent growth rate a year earlier, a leading U.S.
information company said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Releasing the 1999 International Target Cities Report, the New
York-based Thomson Financial Investor Relations said London and
New York led the top 5 cities in the world, with each city
controlling over 2.0 trillion dollars in equity.
</P>
<P>
They were followed by Boston, Tokyo and San Francisco. (Global-
Equity Holdings)
