<HEADLINE> Thailand's Inflation Runs at Lowest Rate For 15 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Inflation is running at
its lowest monthly level for 15 years and Last month's inflation
rate stood at minus 0.5 percent compared a year earlier, according
to figures released by the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
For the first five months, inflation was running at 1.5 percent
year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
The May figure was the lowest since minus 1.6 percent was
recorded in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Inflation was likely to decline further because of the
government's attempts to reduce or hold production costs including
electricity and cooking gas prices, as well as the cut in
value-added tax to 7 percent from 10 percent, Suchai Jaovisidha,
the internal trade department chief, was quoted Wednesday by the
Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
Inflation is expected to increase in the last quarter of this
year, or the first three months of next year at the latest, Suchai
added. 
</P>
