<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Increase in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in the first
quarter of this year in Cambodia recorded a 19 percent increase
over the same period of last year, according to the Ministry of
Tourism's recent statistics.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourist arrivals in the first quarter reached
62,209, raising optimism about the outlook for the whole year.
</P>
<P>
Tourism officials attributed the rise to stability in Cambodia,
which is luring more tourists here. In addition, visitors are
beginning to stay longer in Cambodia than before because more
destinations in the country are accessible.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the visitors were from Asia. The United
States was the country which sent the most visitors to Cambodia
with about 11.5 percent of all visitors during the first three
months of the year, followed by France, China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Tourism expects Cambodia to be one of the
region's fastest-growing destination now that the country is a
full member of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The ministry has predicted a 25 percent annual growth in
tourism for the next 10 years. 
</P>
