<HEADLINE> UN Should Play Due Role in Kosovo Issue: Foreign Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The UN Security Council should play
its due role in resolving the Kosovo issue, Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan said here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark at a meeting with the press shortly after
the talks between Tang and his Russian counterpart Igor Ivanov.
</P>
<P>
Both sides believe that the opinions of the Yugoslav Federation
should be fully heard in any plans to settle the issue, Tang added.
</P>
<P>
He said that both China and Russia had agreed to further
consultations and coordination on the international issues,
including the Kosovo crisis, and to work together to safeguard
world peace and oppose power politics in the future.
</P>
<P>
Sharing Tang's view, Ivanov said Russia and China agreed to
help strengthen the role of the UN in international affairs. The
two countries felt uneasy about the trend pursuing power politics
and mono-polar world, Ivanov added, noting that Russia and China,
both as permanent members of the UN Security Council, would
enhance cooperation to resist such dangerous trend. 
</P>
