<HEADLINE> PLA Air Force Launches Rescue Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A special plane from the Chinese
People's Liberation Army Air Force departed an airport in the
western suburbs of Beijing this morning bound for northwest
China's Qinghai Province to transport a French tourist suffering
from an acute illness to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Jean Escalon, 63, accompanied by his nephew Cancel Fradirec,
arrived in Golmud, a city in northwest Qinghai Province during a
bicycle tour. On May 31, however, Escalon felt a sharp pain in his
lower back.
</P>
<P>
Escalon was immediately hospitalized in Golmud, with a
preliminary diagnosis indicating he was suffering from renal colic
resulting from kidney stones.
</P>
<P>
The hospital was unable to alleviate the pain and his nephew
requested assistance from Asia Emergency Assistance (AEA)
International PTE Limited. AEA consulted with relevant departments
and it was decided that the PLA Air Force would transfer Escalon
to Beijing for further medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Escalon and his nephew planned to cycle to Lhasa, the capital
of southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. The only Qinghai
land route leading to Lhasa runs through Golmud, a city some 2,000
km from Beijing by air. 
</P>
