<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Students Warned Against U.K. University Offers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan students have been
warned against offers for entry into British universities at
exorbitant prices, officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
They said that Sri Lankans domiciled in London have reported
that a group of international racketeers have been making such
offers to students from developing countries, particularly in Asia
and Africa.
</P>
<P>
Based in India, Singapore and Hong Kong, the agents of these
racketeers offer places in British universities for students to
follow courses in accountancy, finance and management science.
</P>
<P>
The students are asked to pay exorbitant fees to obtain a
letter of confirmation from the universities concerned so as to
obtain the necessary visas for travel to Britain.
</P>
<P>
It is only after arrival in Britain that the students realize
they had been duped and had paid excessive fees to the agents.
</P>
<P>
Officials warned parents who spend their life's savings on a
better future for their children not to fall prey to these
international racketeers.
</P>
<P>
Parents and students should be extra careful in remitting money
for international study courses here or abroad, they added.
</P>
