<HEADLINE> MOMEP Completes Task in Peru-Ecuador Border Peace-keeping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Claudio Barbosa de Figueiredo, MOMEP
general coordinator, expressed his satisfaction at the fact that "
the assigned task has been fulfilled and set an example for all
the peace missions in the world."
</P>
<P>
He added that the MOMEP was no longer needed for it was certain
that there would be no more confrontations in the border areas.
</P>
<P>
MOMEP, which started its activities on March 12, 1995, after a
military confrontation in the Ecuador and Peru border, will start
Wednesday the demobilization of its personnel, and by next June 30,
its 115 members will be back to their own countries, Barbosa said.
</P>
<P>
Besides the general coordinator and liaison officials from the
two countries, the mission, whose operations ceased on May 13, was
made up of 92 military officers from Argentina, Brazil, Chile and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
MOMEP performed during the four years 351 control missions in
the border posts, 251 verifications of absence of forces and 390
air patrols. 
</P>
