<DOCNO> XIE19990602.0292 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portugal's Economy Predicted to Grow by 3 Percent in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's economy is expected to
grow by three percent this year, 0.3 to 0.5 points lower than the
target set by the government, the Central Bank predicted in a
report on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the slowdown to a drop in domestic demand
and private spending and a cut in the country's trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
Investment is to rise by five percent in 1999, half the margin
of 1998, while exports and imports are to rise by 4.5 and seven
percent as compared to 8.8 and 14.7 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
Domestic demand is to grow by four to 4.5 percent as compared
to six to seven percent in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
