<HEADLINE> Latin American Steel Output Drops 8.2 Percent in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A local newspaper Tuesday quoted the Brazilian Steel Institute
(IBS) as saying that Latin American steel production in March was
4.1 million tons, a 7.8 percent drop from the same month last year,
which stood at 4.5 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, the biggest producer of steel in Latin America, made 6.
07 million tons of steel in the first quarter of this year,
dropping 3.7 percent compared to 6.3 million tons for the first
three-month period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Mexico, the second largest steel producer in Latin America,
produced 3.7 million tons in the first three months, a slight
reduction from the first quarter of 1998. 
</P>
