<HEADLINE> 16th Men's Handball World Championship Opens in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The 16th Men's Handball World
Championship opened on Tuesday in the Egyptian capital of Cairo.
This is the first time an African country hosts the championship.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak attended the opening ceremony
held in the Cairo Stadium, which has 20,000 seats. Mubarak
announced the start of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
In the preliminary match after the opening ceremony, the
Egyptian team, which finished sixth in the 15th world championship,
beat the Brazilian team 28-19.
</P>
<P>
Besides Egypt and Brazil, other 22 countries also take part in
the tournament. They are scheduled to begin the preliminary
matches on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 24 teams are divided into four groups. The preliminary
matches of Groups A and B will be held in Cairo, the other two
groups will hold the matches respectively in Ismailia at the
middle of the Suez Canal and the Mediterranean Port Said.
</P>
<P>
According to rules, the top four of each group will be
qualified for the next stage which adopts a knock-out system.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team is in Group D, which also includes the teams
of Sweden, France, Yugoslavia, South Korea and Australia. This is
the second time the Chinese team is qualified for the world
championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
