<HEADLINE> Argentine International Reserves Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Argentine Central Bank (
BCRA) announced Tuesday that the country's international reserves
dropped more than 1.6 billion U.S. dollars in the last 15 days.
</P>
<P>
Liquid reserves diminished from 25.669 billion dollars on May
12 to 23.893 billion dollars on May 26. The biggest loss occurred
on May 17, when liquid reserves shrank 896 million dollars, said
BCRA.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from BCRA show a drop of more than two billion
dollars compared to the level before Brazil devaluated its
currency.
</P>
<P>
Total reserves of the Argentine financial system adds up to 32.
057 billion dollars, when legal reserves abroad are included.
</P>
