<HEADLINE> Vince Carter Heads NBA All-Rookie First Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Toronto Raptors guard-forward
Vince Carter heads the NBA's All-Rookie First Team, released today.
</P>
<P>
Carter and Boston Celtics forward Paul Pierce were unanimous
choices, getting named on the First Team ballot of all voters for
the maximum total of 56 points.
</P>
<P>
The 29 NBA coaches get to vote, but not for their own players.
Two points are awarded for a vote to the First Team and one point
for a nod on the Second Team.
</P>
<P>
Sacramento Kings point guard Jason Williams missed unanimity by
one point. Guard Mike Bibby of the Vancouver Grizzlies and forward
Matt Harpring of the Orlando Magic, with 47 and 35 points,
respectively, round out the First Team.
</P>
<P>
The second team is headed by the Houston Rockets' backcourt of
Michael Dickerson and Cuttino Mobley. Harping's teammate, center
Michael Doleac, joined the top pick overall, center Michael
Olowokandi of the Los Angeles Clippers, and forward Antawn Jamison
of the Golden State Warriors on the second team. 
