<HEADLINE> British Committee Says NATO Changing Tactics in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A British committee said on Tuesday
that NATO had changed its tactics on Yugoslavia and was violating
Geneva Conventions.
</P>
<P>
"NATO has changed tack in recent days. It has intensified its
bombing of civilian targets," Alice Mahon, Parliament Member(MP)
from the Labor Party who chairs the Committee for Peace in the
Balkans, said in a statement issued on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said NATO "is now violating the Geneva
Conventions on the protection of civilian life on a routine daily
basis".
</P>
<P>
"The slaughter of 50 innocent civilians in 24 hours by NATO now
does not even produce an apology from (NATO spokesman) Jamie
Shea," Mahon said while commenting on the bombing by NATO on
Monday of a hospital in Surdulica, which resulted in at least 18
deaths.
</P>
<P>
"NATO's new strategy seems to be to terrorize and Brutalize the
civilian population of Yugoslavia," she said.
</P>
<P>
Alice Mahon, who has just returned from the NATO Parliamentary
Assembly in Warsaw, also said that NATO's military actions against
Yugoslavia were widely criticized in NATO countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
