<HEADLINE> U.S. Firms to Equip Japanese Companies with E-Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A leading U.S. business computing
company and a U.S. consulting firm on Tuesday announced alliance
to create the borderless E-commerce infrastructure for Japanese
companies.
</P>
<P>
The two U.S. firms are Computer Associates International Inc.
(CA), world leader in mission-critical business computing, and
Ernst &AMP; Young Consulting Japan Co. (EYCJ), the worldwide-known
consulting firm.
</P>
<P>
They will offer a number of value-added E-commerce, multimedia,
and other technology-based products and services.
</P>
<P>
The two plan to initially focus on providing solutions and
services for Japan's financial services, logistics and
telecommunication industries, CA sources said.
</P>
<P>
The finance business arena requires highly intensive
transaction processing services for Web-based electronic
settlement which must be tightly integrated with a well-managed
information technology infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Japanese firms and organizations are increasingly seen deploy
distributed systems for full-scale E-commerce and other
mission-critical applications for success in today's digital
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
